com.edugility.nomen

Class NameSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.edugility.nomen.NameSupport

  • public class NameSupport
extends Object
    An object that manages Names on behalf of some Named. A NameSupport can be used as an internal delegate in your Named implementation to handle common use cases.
    Author:
    Laird Nelson

      NameSupport(Named delegate)
      Creates a new NameSupport that will manage Names for the supplied Named.

      • getNames

        public <K extends NameType,V extends Name> Set<? extends Map.Entry<K,V>> getNames(Map<K,V> map)
        Returns a non-null, immutable Set of Map.Entry instances, whose keys are NameTypes and whose values are Names as found in the supplied Map.

        This method never returns null.

        Type Parameters:
        K - a type extending NameType
        V - a type extending Name

        Returns:

      • putName

        public Name putName(Map<NameType,Name> map,
                    NameType nameType,
                    Name name)
        Puts the supplied Name into the supplied Map indexed under the supplied NameType, while ensuring that Name ownership is sanely managed.

        This method may return null.

        Parameters:
        map - a mutable Map containing Names indexed by NameTypes; must not be null; this Map will be modified as a result of invoking this method
        nameType - the NameType under which to index the supplied Name in the supplied Map; must not be null
        name - the Name to index in the supplied Map; must not be null
        Returns:
        the Name previously indexed under the supplied NameType, or null

      • removeName

        public Name removeName(Map<?,? extends Name> map,
                       NameType nameType)
        Removes any Name present in the supplied Map that is indexed under the supplied NameType.

        This method may return null.

        Parameters:
        map - the Map from which a Name should be removed; may be null in which case no action will be taken and null will be returned
        nameType - the NameType identifying the Name to be removed; must not be null
        Returns:
        the Name that was removed, or null
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if nameType is null
